<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Phrase 1 (mm. 1–4): Sparse open-fifth entry (I root: C-G). LH C2-G2-C3 throughout.
  Grows from 2-note RH to 3-note LH chords. Pattern "33" root pos mostly.
- Phrase 2 (mm. 5–8): Ascending RH arpeggio in m.5 (C4→E4→G4→C5). Chromatic chords
  (E major, Bm) substituted with nearest diatonic: Em and vii°.
- Phrase 3 (mm. 9–13): Full-texture refrain. RH reaches into high register (C5-E5 in m.10).
  LH gains 4th note in m.10 and m.13. Final I voicing C2-G2-C3-E3.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- Inner alto line (RH upper voice) descends stepwise through the final cadence: D5→C5→B4 (mm. 10-12).
- LH bass moves by fourths/fifths: C→G→F→A→E→G→G→C — smooth root progression.
- m.7 inner vi/iii alternation mirrors the melody's B-C rocking figure.
- m.11 has fast harmonic rhythm (one chord per beat) — the only such measure, for climactic drive.

TEXTURE ARC:
- mm. 1–2: 2-voice opening — sparse entry, light
- mm. 3–4: 3-voice LH added — building
- mm. 5–6: RH arpeggio motion — momentum
- mm. 7–8: chromatic substitutions create inner suspense
- mm. 9–10: full V→I cadential gesture, widest range
- mm. 11–12: one-chord-per-beat drive to final cadence
- m. 13: root-position resolution, pedal C1 reinforces bottom
-->
